      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for the comment. It makes sense that \"SetDefaults\" does not indicate that it should be called after non-default values are set. Actually the original name \"DeriveDefaults\" seems to be better in this regard. So let me keep the name as-is and just update the comments.\n\nFYI, I chose not to follow your suggestions for the reasons below:\n\n\u003e How about;\n\u003e - Use different name, like FillEmptyMembersToDefault (or something better) etc. to represent what it does a bit clearer.\n\nI\u0027m afraid that \"FillEmptyMembersToDefault\" is no better than \"SetDefaults\" in the aspect you raised; it doesn\u0027t alarm me at all even if I attempt to call it for a brand-new Config struct. \"DeriveDefaults\" is better here because it says that default values are derived from something else.\n\n\u003e - Take another approach. E.g., defines getter methods which look up other field to calculate default value if necessary.\n\nI don\u0027t think such refactoring is worthwhile.",
